nutrition:
  calories: 710 kcal
  fat: 36 g
  saturated fat: 15 g
  carbohydrates: 58 g
  sugar: 8 g
  protein: 31 g
  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 1810 mg
servings: 2
time required: 15 minutes
cuisine: Southern Europe
author: HelloFresh
---

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice half the @cucumber{1}(trimmed) into rounds. Halve @tomato{1}; thinly slice into half-moons. Halve @lemon{1}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine sliced cucumber, tomato, half the @dried oregano{1%tsp}, juice from whole lemon, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}.

Pat @fully cooked beef meatballs{8%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; cut into quarters. Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add meatballs, @shawarma spice blend{1%tbsp}, and @water{1/4%cup}; cook, stirring occasionally, until liquid has reduced and meatballs are browned and warmed through, ~{3-5%minutes}. Season with @salt{}. Remove from heat and cover to keep warm.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @feta cheese{1/2%cup}, @sour cream{1.5%tbsp}, @water{1%tbsp}, and a drizzle of olive oil. Season with salt and @pepper{} to taste.

Wrap @pita bread{2} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{10-15%seconds}; halve crosswise.

Fill pitas with cucumber salad, meatballs, and as much feta sauce as you like. Divide between plates and serve.

> To fit in more filling, lay pitas flat before stuffing!